  , issueBody =
      Just
        "http://www.rethinkdb.com/docs/start-on-startup/ 's section \"Startup with systemd\" doesn't mention that you need to configure a data directory in the configuration.\r\nIf you don't do this I'm not sure what the default path will be, but it's probably not what users expect.\r\n\r\nThe guide just says \"Then, copy the sample configuration file and use the configuration file documentation as a guide to customize it.\" but it doesn't say which options specifically you have to configure.\r\nThe relevant option here is `directory=/path/to/your/rethinkdb/directory`.\r\n\r\nAnother problem is that the guide says:\r\n> First, create the RethinkDB data directory with the following command:\r\n> `rethinkdb create -d /path/to/your/rethinkdb/directory`\r\n\r\nbut you also have to change the permissions so that the data directory can be accessed by the `rethinkdb` user:\r\n```\r\nsudo chown -R rethinkdb.rethinkdb /path/to/your/rethinkdb/directory\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nA user on our Google group ran into this I think:\r\nhttps://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/rethinkdb/ic4uICkFjew"
